<p>Alex Grzankowski, currently reader in philosophy at <a href="https://www.bbk.ac.uk/school/historical-studies/study-philosophy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Birkbeck, University of London</a>, has accepted a position at <a href="https://www.kcl.ac.uk/philosophy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">King&#8217;s College London</a> (KCL), where he will be Senior Lecturer in Mind and Metaphysics.<span id="more-54154"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-54158 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/grzankowski-alex.jpg" alt="" width="540" height="515" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/grzankowski-alex.jpg 540w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/grzankowski-alex-300x286.jpg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/grzankowski-alex-400x381.jpg 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px" /></p>
<p><a href="https://alexgrzankowski.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dr. Grzankowski</a> works in philosophy of mind, philosophy of language, metaphysics, and epistemology. You can learn more about his research <a href="https://alexgrzankowski.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/alex-grzankowski" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>Grzankowski is also currently the Associate Director at the <a href="https://philosophy.sas.ac.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Institute of Philosophy, University of London</a>. Once at KCL, he will continue part-time atthe Institute where he will continue to lead the <a href="https://www.ai-humanity-london.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">London AI and Humanity Project</a>.</p>
<p>He takes up his new position at KCL in September.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/06/20/grzankowski-from-birkbeck-to-kings/">Grzankowski from Birkbeck to King’s</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>